1
00:00:00,700 --> 00:00:02,030
Men!

2
00:00:03,080 --> 00:00:04,040
Sparkle-nyan!

3
00:00:04,040 --> 00:00:05,310
Sparkle-nyan!

4
00:00:05,830 --> 00:00:09,600
It is I, Nichiya, at the Queen's service!

5
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:47,290
We Royal Guard gave chase to two Fallen 
Exceeds and headed toward the Edolas Royal City.

6
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:54,800
But those sick, foul-perfumed humans dared 
bare their claws at us, nay, at our Queen herself!

7
00:01:55,050 --> 00:02:02,330
And in just a flash, we Royal Guards were 
all transformed into a lacrima, and captured!

8
00:02:02,650 --> 00:02:08,810
The King of Edolas, Faust, is trying to 
use Dragon Slayer Magic to attack Extalia!

9
00:02:09,810 --> 00:02:10,760
Men!

10
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:14,930
I must do something!

11
00:02:15,850 --> 00:02:18,960
But right now, I am in this sorry state!

12
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:21,530
Somebody, turn me back to normal!

13
00:02:21,790 --> 00:02:23,700
Men!

14
00:02:25,950 --> 00:02:30,600
Code ETD. Exceed Total Destruction.

15
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:33,560
Operation: Extermination of Angels, is it?

16
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:36,580
Finally, it's time for the main event.

17
00:02:37,450 --> 00:02:40,160
For the time being, I'll relay 
this information to them.

18
00:02:41,590 --> 00:02:43,610
Attention, citizens of Edolas.

19
00:02:43,610 --> 00:02:47,650
Thank you very much for 
visiting E-Land today.

20
00:02:47,650 --> 00:02:51,230
From the Hell's Coaster 
to the Monster Academy,

21
00:02:51,230 --> 00:02:58,330
our King Faust has come up with a variety 
of attractions using unlimited magic power,

22
00:02:58,330 --> 00:03:00,240
all for your enjoyment!

23
00:03:02,780 --> 00:03:05,070
Coco, wait, would you?!

24
00:03:08,970 --> 00:03:10,750
Hurry up and give me the key!

25
00:03:12,190 --> 00:03:14,530
I won't give any of them to you!

26
00:03:17,810 --> 00:03:20,510
'Cause I'll beat him!

27
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:25,130
The Great River 
of Stars is for Pride.

28
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:30,330
You're an Earthland wizard.

29
00:03:30,330 --> 00:03:32,070
What are you doing here?

30
00:03:32,430 --> 00:03:35,130
What has happened to Hughes and Sugar Boy?

31
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:37,960
I wonder if Natsu is okay?

32
00:03:38,490 --> 00:03:41,320
But, I can't leave this girl alone.

33
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:44,200
Why is he after my keys?

34
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,910
Hurry and give me the key!

35
00:03:49,950 --> 00:03:52,090
Sheesh, there it is!

36
00:03:52,090 --> 00:03:54,000
Eww, what a lecherous stare!

37
00:03:55,710 --> 00:03:57,210
I won't give you this key!

38
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:01,110
*bishi*

39
00:04:01,450 --> 00:04:02,760
What's *bishi*?

40
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:06,240
I think she's confused...

41
00:04:07,850 --> 00:04:09,640
Crumble to pieces!

42
00:04:12,140 --> 00:04:14,290
What're we gonna do, Gajeel?

43
00:04:14,290 --> 00:04:17,200
This fight's been completely one-sided!

44
00:04:17,970 --> 00:04:20,530
But the fun's only started, see!

45
00:04:20,930 --> 00:04:23,070
I cannot allow that to 
pass without a response...

46
00:04:28,070 --> 00:04:32,570
Taking a "wait-and-see" approach? 
You make light of me.

47
00:04:32,570 --> 00:04:34,450
The hell I am!

48
00:04:34,450 --> 00:04:37,530
I'm just takin' my time having 
a taste of your power.

49
00:04:37,530 --> 00:04:40,590
Gajeel, that was so mean! 
I'm not just some object!

50
00:04:40,590 --> 00:04:42,100
Don't chuck me!

51
00:04:42,100 --> 00:04:45,240
I saved your ass, so no complaining!

52
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:47,050
Anyway, you're in the way!

53
00:04:47,050 --> 00:04:50,930
If you're gonna dart around, 
I'll finish you off first!

54
00:04:51,310 --> 00:04:53,980
He's so mean... He's so scary...

55
00:04:53,980 --> 00:04:56,420
Okay, that's enough of our comedy act.

56
00:04:56,420 --> 00:04:58,620
Let's finally get things 
started for real, shall we?

57
00:04:59,110 --> 00:05:01,830
Just try it, Earthland wizard!

58
00:05:02,850 --> 00:05:05,080
I hope everyone's okay...

59
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:07,280
I'm worried about the future.

60
00:05:08,270 --> 00:05:10,700
Gate of the Giant Bull, I open thee!

61
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,330
Taurus!

62
00:05:19,150 --> 00:05:22,450
That outfit is the best ever, Lucy-san!

63
00:05:22,450 --> 00:05:24,540
So much for your cool entrance.

64
00:05:24,540 --> 00:05:27,380
What's that?! A cow?!

65
00:05:27,850 --> 00:05:30,040
That's Earthland magic?

66
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:33,510
But, he seems like a pervert...

67
00:05:33,510 --> 00:05:36,180
What about my reward from before?

68
00:05:36,180 --> 00:05:39,030
Make this guy beg for mercy, 
and I'll think about it!

69
00:05:39,030 --> 00:05:39,850
Go!

70
00:05:39,850 --> 00:05:44,430
Beg for mercy!

71
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:48,950
He's faster than he looks!

72
00:05:48,950 --> 00:05:51,450
"Hii" ain't begging for mercy!

73
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:53,790
But, how?

74
00:05:53,790 --> 00:05:56,960
She creates something from 
nothing at all? Preposterous!

75
00:05:57,550 --> 00:05:59,830
I cannot analyze it... How?

76
00:05:59,830 --> 00:06:01,880
Ready, set... Beg!

77
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:02,930
Impudent!

78
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:09,220
Flame Liquid!

79
00:06:09,220 --> 00:06:10,650
Taurus!

80
00:06:10,650 --> 00:06:12,550
What was that magic now?

81
00:06:12,550 --> 00:06:14,730
Watch out for that liquid!

82
00:06:15,950 --> 00:06:17,730
I'm fresh out...

83
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:24,570
Storm Liquid!

84
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:26,080
Gate...

85
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:30,450
...of the Maiden, I open thee!

86
00:06:31,660 --> 00:06:33,090
Virgo!

87
00:06:34,370 --> 00:06:36,410
It's another something!

88
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:39,080
Is it a similar effect as Anima?

89
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:41,590
You will receive punishment!

90
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:45,280
Spica Hole!

91
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:46,380
What?

92
00:06:50,970 --> 00:06:52,190
All right!

93
00:06:52,430 --> 00:06:53,510
Wow...

94
00:06:53,510 --> 00:06:55,120
Princess, time for punishment?

95
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,330
Why?!

96
00:06:56,610 --> 00:06:59,390
Plus, she's a princess!

97
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:02,480
Maybe I should hand her this key...

98
00:07:03,250 --> 00:07:06,110
But then, the eternal magic power...

99
00:07:06,530 --> 00:07:10,200
But if the King gets it back, Lily's life...

100
00:07:11,310 --> 00:07:12,570
What'll I do?

101
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,630
What's that?

102
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:17,910
Is that your stomach grumbling, Princess?

103
00:07:17,910 --> 00:07:19,000
Now, look here...

104
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,460
Punishment?

105
00:07:27,910 --> 00:07:30,680
I've got you, Coco!

106
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:34,390
What the heck is that?

107
00:07:34,390 --> 00:07:35,990
An octopus tentacle, Princess.

108
00:07:35,990 --> 00:07:37,760
That's not what I meant!

109
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:39,810
Octopus Liquid!

110
00:07:40,340 --> 00:07:43,230
I drank it myself!

111
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:53,910
Now, no matter what strange magic 
you might use, none of it will work!

112
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:56,030
I-I wonder about that...

113
00:07:56,030 --> 00:07:58,500
Princess, I don't think it will work.

114
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:00,370
Don't give up before we even try!

115
00:08:04,340 --> 00:08:06,880
I've got Coco.

116
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:10,340
But I won't be satisfied until I've 
exterminated you, insolent brat!

117
00:08:10,340 --> 00:08:11,950
This guy holds a grudge!

118
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:14,050
Princess, you have terrible 
luck with guys, don't you?

119
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:17,830
That comment wasn't necessary!

120
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:22,630
Get me down!

121
00:08:22,890 --> 00:08:24,770
Princess, take this!

122
00:08:29,030 --> 00:08:30,070
What is it?

123
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:33,280
It's a Spirit World whip that 
can extend and contract.

124
00:08:33,580 --> 00:08:36,240
Eridanus's Fleuve d'Etoile.

125
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,680
The river of stars?

126
00:08:38,230 --> 00:08:41,550
I hope it is of help. Although I 
don't think it'll be effective.

127
00:08:41,550 --> 00:08:44,040
Why are you so negative about it?

128
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:48,000
We won't know till we try, right?

129
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,920
You brat! Come 'ere!

130
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:55,030
I wish you best of health 
in your battle, Princess!

131
00:08:55,340 --> 00:08:56,930
Here I go!

132
00:09:01,430 --> 00:09:03,350
What's this?

133
00:09:03,350 --> 00:09:05,520
Something like that ain't gonna work!

134
00:09:10,610 --> 00:09:12,800
See? See?

135
00:09:13,290 --> 00:09:16,240
That didn't even tickle!

136
00:09:21,350 --> 00:09:25,210
What's wrong, Earthland wizard?

137
00:09:25,210 --> 00:09:29,210
What happened to the whole 
"I'll beat you" thing, huh?

138
00:09:29,210 --> 00:09:31,040
It really didn't work!

139
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:32,770
This thing is totally useless!

140
00:09:32,770 --> 00:09:33,800
What's wrong?

141
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:36,670
You can't use any more freaky magic?

142
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:39,510
Magic?

143
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:44,970
If I call multiple Spirits in a row, 
it quickly drains my magic power.

144
00:09:45,890 --> 00:09:46,770
That's right!

145
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:49,900
So that's why Virgo gave me this!

146
00:09:52,710 --> 00:09:53,840
Thank you...

147
00:09:55,990 --> 00:10:00,740
I really appreciate how you 
Spirits take care of me!

148
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:04,410
Just stand there and be squashed!

149
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:07,960
If I remember right, she said 
it could expand and contract!

150
00:10:15,210 --> 00:10:15,920
What?

151
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,140
Let her go!

152
00:10:23,690 --> 00:10:26,220
She belongs to our army!

153
00:10:26,220 --> 00:10:29,650
<i>You</i> have nothing to do with this!

154
00:10:30,060 --> 00:10:31,650
You're hurting her!

155
00:10:31,650 --> 00:10:34,440
And if I do this, I'll hurt her even more!

156
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:36,570
Look here, you...

157
00:10:37,610 --> 00:10:41,280
Stop flitting around my body!

158
00:10:42,070 --> 00:10:45,370
If she's one of you, shouldn't 
you be protecting her?

159
00:10:48,030 --> 00:10:52,540
I'll never lose to someone who 
doesn't even understand that!

160
00:10:53,460 --> 00:10:54,770
My leg!

161
00:10:55,070 --> 00:10:56,860
When did she...?

162
00:11:00,970 --> 00:11:03,030
I swear on the name of my guild!

163
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:06,080
You little brat!

164
00:11:06,490 --> 00:11:09,270
What the... It's hot!

165
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:14,860
A real monster, huh?

166
00:11:14,860 --> 00:11:18,780
I'm not a damn monster, you freak!

167
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,570
Natsu!

168
00:11:47,820 --> 00:11:50,690
Bydo and Hughes have been beaten!

169
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:57,980
What's that giant thing?

170
00:11:58,220 --> 00:11:59,730
Great job there, Natsu!

171
00:12:00,260 --> 00:12:02,580
Huh? Someone's collapsed...

172
00:12:02,990 --> 00:12:04,540
Are you okay?

173
00:12:04,540 --> 00:12:05,730
You know her?

174
00:12:05,730 --> 00:12:07,780
Not exactly.

175
00:12:09,050 --> 00:12:09,790
What is it?

176
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,600
What's wrong?

177
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:12,580
You got a stomachache?

178
00:12:12,580 --> 00:12:13,660
Why'd you think that?

179
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:18,920
This key is to a device that 
will kill your friends.

180
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:20,400
What the...

181
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:24,230
You mean, the one that'll ram 
the lacrima into Extalia?

182
00:12:24,650 --> 00:12:27,170
So <i>that's</i> the key he was after?

183
00:12:29,740 --> 00:12:35,520
I'd rather we all live in peace than 
have an infinite supply of magic.

184
00:12:36,150 --> 00:12:40,730
So... please, destroy this key!

185
00:12:42,650 --> 00:12:44,180
Please!

186
00:12:45,190 --> 00:12:47,560
Which means, all we have to do is break this,

187
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:50,410
and we can stop them from 
attacking with the lacrima!

188
00:12:50,410 --> 00:12:51,330
Thanks!

189
00:12:51,330 --> 00:12:53,370
Okay! Leave it to me!

190
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:56,170
What?!

191
00:12:59,420 --> 00:13:03,490
Now, now, Coco. You mustn't give something 
as important as this to the enemy!

192
00:13:03,490 --> 00:13:05,260
I must return it to our Highness.

193
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:07,380
Sugar Boy!

194
00:13:07,380 --> 00:13:08,680
The key!

195
00:13:08,680 --> 00:13:09,510
Oh, no!

196
00:13:09,510 --> 00:13:11,310
Give it back!

197
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:14,390
You bastard! Hold it right there!

198
00:13:15,710 --> 00:13:17,110
You again?

199
00:13:17,110 --> 00:13:18,400
You ain't gettin' away!

200
00:13:19,420 --> 00:13:20,390
Gray!

201
00:13:20,390 --> 00:13:21,730
Natsu, Lucy!

202
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:24,660
That chinny idiot is mine!

203
00:13:24,660 --> 00:13:26,100
Don't you go butting in!

204
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:28,620
In other words, leave the rest to me!

205
00:13:29,930 --> 00:13:33,570
Quite persistent, you are. Even though 
there's no chance for you to win...

206
00:13:33,570 --> 00:13:35,930
Shut up! Now, stop right there!

207
00:13:35,930 --> 00:13:38,130
I'm in a hurry!

208
00:13:38,980 --> 00:13:41,050
Rossa Espada...

209
00:13:45,130 --> 00:13:47,250
We'll head after 'im, too!

210
00:13:47,250 --> 00:13:49,380
We've got to get that key back!

211
00:13:50,460 --> 00:13:51,890
What's this?

212
00:13:51,890 --> 00:13:53,000
This again?

213
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,250
What's going on, seriously?

214
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:57,710
Crap! I can't move!

215
00:13:57,710 --> 00:13:59,550
Lucy, do something about this!

216
00:13:59,550 --> 00:14:03,020
At times like this... Fleuve d'Etoile!

217
00:14:03,020 --> 00:14:04,080
...huh?

218
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:10,530
Octopus! It's in my way! And heavy! And icky!

219
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:18,480
All attractions have been closed for today.

220
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:20,960
We'll be awaiting your next visit.

221
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:22,170
No!

222
00:14:26,930 --> 00:14:28,260
Hold it!

223
00:14:28,260 --> 00:14:31,890
And how are you sliding 
along in the first place?

224
00:14:33,780 --> 00:14:35,290
I don't know either!

225
00:14:35,290 --> 00:14:36,720
O-Oh, I see.

226
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:39,780
So anyway, what is that key?

227
00:14:39,780 --> 00:14:42,810
It's the key to activate 
the Dragon Chain Cannon.

228
00:14:42,810 --> 00:14:43,730
Dragon Chain?

229
00:14:43,730 --> 00:14:47,030
Uh-oh! The rest is a secret.

230
00:14:47,030 --> 00:14:48,860
Dragon Chain Cannon... Dragon?

231
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:51,910
It must be about the Dragon 
Slayer Magic they stole!

232
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:55,860
If I remember right, Wendy told us about it.

233
00:14:55,860 --> 00:14:59,930
They're going to speed up the floating island 
with the lacrima on it with Dragon Slayer Magic,

234
00:14:59,930 --> 00:15:03,730
and ram it into Extalia. That's 
what the Kingdom is planning.

235
00:15:03,730 --> 00:15:05,130
That's what she said.

236
00:15:05,130 --> 00:15:08,530
This is something that 
we cannot let you have.

237
00:15:09,610 --> 00:15:13,020
Which means we can't let you 
take it from us, either!

238
00:15:13,020 --> 00:15:15,270
Ice Make Floor!

239
00:15:16,810 --> 00:15:20,020
Ice isn't going to win against me...

240
00:15:20,020 --> 00:15:22,390
It makes anything it touches flexible!

241
00:15:22,390 --> 00:15:24,090
Rossa Espada!

242
00:15:29,190 --> 00:15:32,240
Even if it's flexible, it 
still has the same properties!

243
00:15:32,240 --> 00:15:35,160
Properties like "ice floors are slippery"!

244
00:15:41,370 --> 00:15:43,270
I told you that wouldn't work!

245
00:15:47,090 --> 00:15:48,460
The key?

246
00:15:48,460 --> 00:15:49,920
Time to bust it up!

247
00:16:03,610 --> 00:16:04,410
Huh?

248
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:09,810
It's a bit cold, Ice Boy.

249
00:16:09,810 --> 00:16:12,200
Don't go givin' me weird nicknames!

250
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:14,850
And why? Why won't it break?

251
00:16:14,850 --> 00:16:19,120
Well, isn't it obvious? It's not 
something that's so easy to break.

252
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:21,080
And, it's cold!

253
00:16:22,160 --> 00:16:24,130
Would you be so kind as to let go?

254
00:16:24,130 --> 00:16:27,580
It's not my style to hold 
hands with other men.

255
00:16:28,770 --> 00:16:33,270
Come on, now... Haven't you realized 
our roles are flipped now?

256
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:36,750
What might you mean, Ice Boy?

257
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:38,660
Stop calling me that, sheesh!

258
00:16:38,660 --> 00:16:39,950
Anyway...

259
00:16:40,360 --> 00:16:45,480
You people might need this key, but we don't!

260
00:16:46,730 --> 00:16:50,000
If I can't break it, I'll at least 
make it so you can't use it!

261
00:16:50,940 --> 00:16:52,510
Freeze!

262
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:57,980
Not going to work.

263
00:16:57,980 --> 00:17:02,570
Have you forgotten? The Rossa 
Esparda can make ice flexible.

264
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:07,540
You sure? If you're off just a 
bit, the key'll be a bent-up mess.

265
00:17:10,040 --> 00:17:12,490
I am very meticulous.

266
00:17:12,490 --> 00:17:13,960
What the hell are you saying?!

267
00:17:15,140 --> 00:17:18,640
I see... I should just cut <i>you</i> down!

268
00:17:25,140 --> 00:17:27,280
I told you, it's no use!

269
00:17:29,650 --> 00:17:31,150
You think I'm gonna lose?!

270
00:17:33,080 --> 00:17:36,000
I'll freeze you first!

271
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,250
I won't let go, even if I'm dead!

272
00:17:42,950 --> 00:17:45,040
I'll never let you!

273
00:17:50,460 --> 00:17:52,710
Let go!

274
00:17:52,710 --> 00:17:54,960
Freeze!

275
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:23,080
I-Impossible!

276
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:24,910
The key cracked!

277
00:18:24,910 --> 00:18:27,870
Right, that's the way! I should 
just break it like this!

278
00:18:27,870 --> 00:18:30,000
Oh, no! This is bad!

279
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:32,060
Let go! The key is gonna break!

280
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:34,250
This thing holds the lives 
of my friends hostage!

281
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:37,780
I'm gonna bust it to smithereens!

282
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:40,480
W-Wait!

283
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:42,040
This really is bad!

284
00:18:42,040 --> 00:18:45,350
This key is something that you need!

285
00:18:45,350 --> 00:18:46,640
What did you just say?

286
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:48,700
Whatever, just call a cease-fire for now!

287
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:50,410
The key's gonna break!

288
00:18:51,690 --> 00:18:53,520
What are you talking about?!

289
00:18:56,400 --> 00:19:03,070
W-With this key, you can return 
your friends to the way they were!

290
00:19:06,990 --> 00:19:08,290
You're bluffing.

291
00:19:08,290 --> 00:19:09,950
It's the truth!

292
00:19:09,950 --> 00:19:12,920
The Dragon Chain Cannon shoots 
concentrated Dragon Slayer Magic!

293
00:19:13,730 --> 00:19:19,050
Don't you know what Dragon Slayer 
Magic is used for in this world?

294
00:19:21,740 --> 00:19:25,890
I shattered the lacrima with Dragon 
Slayer Magic to turn you back to normal.

295
00:19:26,550 --> 00:19:28,950
I hear that on this world, 
Dragon Slayer Magic

296
00:19:28,950 --> 00:19:32,970
has the power to restore people 
who have been turned into lacrima.

297
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:41,370
If you shoot the Dragon Chain Cannon into the 
lacrima, your friends will return to how they were!

298
00:19:43,670 --> 00:19:45,620
Understand now?

299
00:19:45,620 --> 00:19:48,550
This key is important to both of us!

300
00:19:48,550 --> 00:19:50,250
You can't destroy it!

301
00:19:52,170 --> 00:19:54,540
We've got Gajeel, though.

302
00:19:54,540 --> 00:19:57,320
And if it comes to it, 
Natsu and Wendy as well!

303
00:19:57,730 --> 00:20:00,540
We've got three Dragon Slayers!

304
00:20:00,930 --> 00:20:03,840
We don't need this damn key!

305
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:06,470
But you don't know how many 
days it'll take, right?

306
00:20:07,350 --> 00:20:10,920
The conversion to magic 
power will begin tomorrow!

307
00:20:10,920 --> 00:20:16,250
Our plan is to ram the lacrima 
into Extalia before that!

308
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:22,060
It's true that with three Dragon 
Slayers, you can likely save many.

309
00:20:22,060 --> 00:20:24,950
However, you can't save them all!

310
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:30,200
If you want to save everyone, 
you cannot destroy this key!

311
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:33,970
Plus, there's a great number 
of people from the city

312
00:20:33,970 --> 00:20:38,710
that have nothing to do with 
the guild in that lacrima, yes?

313
00:20:40,780 --> 00:20:44,200
Now... Let go.

314
00:21:00,260 --> 00:21:02,690
I won't give the key to you!

315
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:19,380
The key!!

316
00:21:19,380 --> 00:21:22,960
Are you a total idiot? I 
wasn't bluffing, you know!

317
00:21:25,670 --> 00:21:30,690
You friends will never come back again!

318
00:21:32,230 --> 00:21:35,880
Yes, they will. I will bring 
them all back, safe and sound!

319
00:21:35,880 --> 00:21:37,990
Back to our guild!

320
00:21:38,760 --> 00:21:42,270
In the space between me and my weapon...

321
00:21:42,540 --> 00:21:46,190
Ice Blade: Seven Strike Dance!

322
00:21:58,740 --> 00:22:01,520
You're nuts, Ice Boy.

323
00:22:01,970 --> 00:22:04,880
You actually destroyed the key...

324
00:22:05,330 --> 00:22:11,050
Even though with that key, you 
could save your friends...

325
00:22:14,070 --> 00:22:18,180
I'm an Ice Maker Magic wizard.

326
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:22,880
I can make as many keys as I need.

327
00:23:55,830 --> 00:23:59,400
We've got the key, so let's go save everyone!

328
00:23:59,670 --> 00:24:01,650
Look, Erza's back!

329
00:24:01,650 --> 00:24:03,450
Hey, Erza!

330
00:24:03,450 --> 00:24:06,470
Wait a sec... Isn't that the Edolas Erza?

331
00:24:06,470 --> 00:24:10,260
Oh, no... Does that mean our Erza lost?

332
00:24:10,260 --> 00:24:13,760
God damn it... After we've come so far...

333
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:16,510
Next time: The Doomsday Dragon Chain Cannon.

334
00:24:16,750 --> 00:24:19,560
What'll we do, Natsu? At 
this rate, everyone...

335
00:24:19,560 --> 00:24:22,070
Not yet... It's not over yet!

336
00:24:22,070 --> 00:24:24,140
We'll save everyone, for sure!

